<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>God I hate it when people mindlessly flame!!!  <BR>
<BR>
Here is a quote of what you said...<BR>
<BR>
Serina Hands down your off your rocker!<BR>
-----<BR>
clerics/druids/shamans ... 3 ac addition does NOT off set<BR>
+3 wis / +3 int <BR>
-----<BR>
leave this thing for the monks, if anything go for the ruined circlet while your<BR>
in Permafrost!!! +4int/+4wis <BR>
-----<BR>
good grief, as much as we ARE NOT MELEE types you would think to get a clue about your role<BR>
and while I am mildly flaming you SHAMANS out there stop using FRENZY you get your druid <BR>
group mates killed, because your trying to be a poor mans TANK!<BR>
<BR>
Kajal Godwin<BR>
<BR>
Okay, first off, you mindless flamer, Serina said that the plus 3 str offsets the weight of 5.  And Serina is right, almost.  The savant cap is less than 2 if I'm not mistaken (and I could be mistaken, hehehe).  Never was it said that the addition all 3 ac offsets 3 wis.  However you will aquire more mana from a +25 mana item than a +3 wis item, until higher levels that is.<BR>
<BR>
Secondly, once again, if I am not mistaken this is CLR/DRU/SHM only!  Not a monk item as you put it!  And the person that asked the question was a level 19 cleric.  Yes for a level 19 cleric this item is far and away better than a savant cap!  Hmm, instead of flaming let's think about this a second.  More AC/MANA/STR...  Sounds like it does win hands down for a cleric.<BR>
<BR>
Now that I have pointed out the errors in your wisdom(?).  Before offering a flame you need to read the post you are flaming.  Comprehend what they are saying before you offer up your pearls of ineptitude.  People were giving this young cleric GOOD advice, till you came along and flamed them, spewing out terrible advice!  READ BEFORE YOU FLAME!!!<BR>
<BR>
Oh and by the way, (this may be way over your head) I did not know trolls could be Druids! hehehehehheh<BR>
<BR>
Now be usefull in your posts or don't post at all.<BR>
<BR>
Sorry, I'll hop off my soap box now.<BR>
