<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Bazil</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-06-07 16:08:54</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Good post Minks, there is a formula for figuring out your mana if you are not sure which one is better. I am level 32 and i get 7 mana per +wisdom, therefore for me the savant cap would give me 21 mana. The way it works is, take your level divided by 5(round down) +1, and thats how you get your mana per +wis. 32 divided by 5 is just over 6(round down to 6) +1 =7<BR>
<BR>
So at level 19 the Cleric would have been foolish to not use the Coronet which is 25 mana, over the savant cap at 12 mana at level 19.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Wakdoktor</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-06-09 13:18:14</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>As I understand the formula, it is (Level+2) divided by 5, with no rounding at all.  You will see your mana rise every level, if you look closely.  But I could be wrong.  So +3 wis would not be as good as +25 mana until level 39.  However, a 19 would not get the full +25 mana, and nobody knows the formula :(<BR>
<BR>
As for this vs. savant's cap for a level 19 cleric, this is a little better, because AC is somewhat more important to a cleric than wisdom.  The "not a melee" rant is 100% off base.  Healing is the biggest taunt in the game, and a good cleric has to take a beating and not heal himself, constantly.  The one thing you don't want a cleric to do is die or zone with mana in his tank.<BR>
<BR>
The one thing that concerns me is the net 1.7 additional weight for the 3AC.  This might well depend on how you are set up, your race, etc.</font></td></tr></table>
